# TimChat domain model and modules

## Domain entities

### Identity and collaboration

- `User`, `UserProfile`
- `Workspace`, `WorkspaceMember`
- `Role`, `PermissionGrant`, `MemberRole`
- `Channel`, `ChannelPermissionOverride`
- `Invite`
- `AttachmentMetadata`

### Chat

- `Message`, `MessageAttachment`, `MessageRevision`, `MessageDeletion`

### Call-control

- `CallSession`, `CallParticipant`, `ParticipantDevice`
- `ParticipantSelfState`, `ParticipantEffectiveState`
- `ModerationAction`, `CallJoinTicket`, `ReconnectToken`

### Realtime operational

- `WebSocketConnection`, `ClientSession`
- `PresenceSnapshot`, `ChannelRealtimeSubscription`, `LiveCallSnapshot`

### Audit

- `AuditEvent`, `AuditActor`, `AuditTarget`, `AuditPayload`

## Backend module structure

Root package: `ru.timchat`

```
ru.timchat
  ├─ TimChatApplication
  ├─ auth          — JWT / OIDC, current user context, handshake auth
  ├─ user          — user profile management
  ├─ workspace     — workspace lifecycle, members, invites
  ├─ permission    — roles, grants, resolution, channel overrides, call policy
  ├─ channel       — channel model, text/voice/video rules, ordering
  ├─ message       — send/edit/delete, history, realtime publication
  ├─ attachment    — metadata, upload/download auth, signed URLs
  ├─ presence      — online/offline/idle/dnd, live projection
  ├─ realtime      — WebSocket transport, protocol, dispatch, handlers, registry
  ├─ call          — call lifecycle, participant lifecycle, self/effective state, snapshots
  ├─ media         — TURN credentials, SFU adapter, media policy
  ├─ moderation    — mute/kick/block actions, enforcement state
  ├─ audit         — durable audit records
  ├─ common        — errors, ids, shared contracts
  └─ infra         — PostgreSQL config, Redis config, storage clients, observability
```

## Internal layering per module

Каждый бизнес-модуль внутри должен следовать структуре:

```
<module>
  ├─ api           — REST DTOs / controllers
  ├─ application   — use cases / orchestration / command services
  ├─ domain        — core model, invariants, repository interfaces
  ├─ infra         — JPA / Redis / storage / SFU implementations
  └─ mapper        — model translations where needed
```

Realtime module имеет свою специфику:

```
realtime
  ├─ ws            — WebSocket transport layer
  ├─ protocol      — envelope parsing, serialization
  ├─ dispatch      — routing incoming messages to handlers
  ├─ handler       — typed handlers per domain scope
  ├─ registry      — connection / session registry
  └─ security      — per-command auth
```

## Правила

- Не создавай модули за пределами этого списка без явного обоснования.
- Не нарушай layering: `api` не лезет в `infra`, `domain` не зависит от `api` или `infra`.
- Не складывай всю логику в один модуль.
- Один модуль = одна bounded area ответственности.
- Use case в application-слое должен читаться как сценарий:
  1. validate auth / permission
  2. update durable state
  3. update transient projection
  4. emit outbound realtime event
  5. write audit if needed
